%N A388008 Number of generalized conjugacy classes in the semigroup of relations on a set of size n.
%C A388008 Let [n] be the set {1, ..., n} and [0] be the empty set. Elements of the semigroup of relations on [n] are subsets of the product [n] X [n]. Given two elements A,B in the semigroup of relations on [n] their product, AB, is defined as the set { (i,j) | there exists a k in [n] such that (i,k) is in A and (k,j) is in B}.
%C A388008 Given a finite monoid M, for each element m in M there exists some positive integer w such that m^w is idempotent. let ~ be the smallest equivalence relation on M such that mn~nm and m^(w+1)~m for all m,n in M. A generalized conjugacy class of M is an equivalence class of the equivalence relation ~.
%C A388008 The definition of generalized conjugacy classes used here can be found in Benjamin Steinberg's "Representation Theory of Finite Monoids" on page 104. Reference below.
%H A388008 Kim Ki-Hang Butler and George Markowsky, <a href="https://koreascience.kr/article/JAKO197225748110852.page">The Number of Maximal Subgroups of The Semigroup of Binary Relations</a>, Kyungpook Mathematical Journal, vol 12 iss 1 (1972), 1-8.
%H A388008 Benjamin Steinberg, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-43932-7">Representation Theory of Finite Monoids</a>, Springer Cham, (2016), 104.
%e A388008 a(0)=1 The only generalized conjugacy class is { {} }.
%e A388008 a(1)=2 The generalized conjugacy classes are { {} }, and { { (1,1) } }.
%e A388008 a(2)=5 The generalized conjugacy classes are { {}, { (1,2) }, { (2,1) } }, { { (1,1) }, { (2,2) }, { (1,1), (1,2) }, { (2,1), (2,2) }, { (1,1), (2,1) }, { (1,2), (2,2) }, { (1,1), (1,2), (2,1) }, { (2,2), (1,2), (2,1) }, { (1,1), (1,2), (2,1), (2,2) } }, { { (1,1), (1,2), (2,2) }, { (1,1), (2,1), (2,2) } }, { { (1,2), (2,1) } }, and { { (1,1), (2,2) } }.
%o A388008 (GAP)
%o A388008 # GAP 4
%o A388008 LoadPackage("semigroups");;
%o A388008 M    := FullBooleanMatMonoid(n);;
%o A388008 MD   := RegularDClasses(M);;
%o A388008 MH   := List(MD ,GroupHClass         );;
%o A388008 MHI  := List(MH ,IsomorphismPermGroup);;
%o A388008 MI   := List(MHI,Images              );;
%o A388008 MCC  := List(MI ,ConjugacyClasses    );;
%o A388008 CMCC := Concatenation(MCC);;
%o A388008 Length(CMCC); # Value of a(n)
